---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Refiner">
  <h1>Refiner</h1>

  <p>Takes a failed evaluation and rewrites only the broken parts of the agent — targeted fixes, not full rewrites.</p>

  <h2>Interface</h2>
  <pre><code>import &lcub; Refiner &rcub; from "agent-forge/refiner";
import &lcub; createOllamaBackend &rcub; from "agent-forge/llm_backend/ollama";

const llm = createOllamaBackend();
const refiner = new Refiner(llm);

const improvedCode = await refiner.refine(&lcub;
  currentCode: agentCodeString,
  scoreReport: scoreReport,
  iteration: 2,
&rcub;);</code></pre>

  <h2>Refinement Prompt Strategy</h2>
  <p>The Refiner's system prompt instructs the LLM to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Read the failure report carefully</li>
    <li>Identify root causes, not just symptoms</li>
    <li>Rewrite <strong>only</strong> the parts that need fixing</li>
    <li>Keep what works — do not rewrite everything</li>
    <li>Preserve the header comment block</li>
    <li>Preserve INPUT_SCHEMA and OUTPUT_SCHEMA</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Failure Report</h2>
  <p>The Refiner receives a human-readable failure summary:</p>
  <pre><code>Failed Tests (3/5):
  - Input: sample input - Missing required output field: "summary"
  - Input: sample input - Tool "gh_api" called incorrectly
  - Input: sample input - Error: Cannot read properties of undefined

Generalization Warning: Agent failed 2/3 generalization holdout tests
Coverage Gaps: style violations</code></pre>

  <h2>Common Fix Patterns</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Detection</th><th>Fix</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Missing fields</td><td>Expected keys not in output</td><td>Add missing keys to return object</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Schema mismatch</td><td>Output key names differ</td><td>Align keys with OUTPUT_SCHEMA</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Uncaught errors</td><td>Subprocess error in TestRunner</td><td>Wrap logic in try/catch</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Tool misuse</td><td>Tool returns unexpected shape</td><td>Fix tool call arguments</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Edge case crash</td><td>Null/undefined access</td><td>Add defensive checks</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Code Extraction</h2>
  <p>After the LLM returns the refined code, the Refiner extracts the agent block by finding <code>// agent:</code> in the output. If extraction fails, the original code is returned with a console warning.</p>

  <h2>Temperature</h2>
  <p>The Refiner uses temperature 0.5 (lower than Generator's 0.7) to produce more deterministic, targeted changes rather than creative rewrites.</p>
</Layout>
